- 1.4.3 | Apr 2026:

-- New Features --
[New] CI workflow: base-os-map input wires BATSMAN_BASE_OS_MAP through to the
      matrix, so consumers using variant→base mappings (e.g., LMD's yara-x →
      debian12) build the correct base Dockerfile in CI. Identity applied to
      OSes without a mapping (backward compatible — omit the input to preserve
      existing behavior).

-- Bug Fixes --
[Fix] BATSMAN_VERSION constant bumped to 1.4.3 — was stale at 1.4.1 across
      the v1.4.2 release; every --version/--help printed the wrong version.
[Fix] file-groups.sh + parallel-mode test discovery: reject .bats filenames not
      matching ^[0-9][a-zA-Z0-9._-]*\.bats$. Closes JSON-injection and
      shell-word-split vectors at the matrix.files boundary that reached
      unquoted shell context downstream.
[Fix] base-os-map charset gate in BOTH file-groups.sh and the local lib
      (BATSMAN_BASE_OS_MAP resolver): reject map entries with whitespace or
      shell-metachars in keys or values — `for entry in $var` IFS-splits and
      a malformed entry would silently yield wrong build targets.
[Fix] CI workflow input hardening: numeric inputs (timeout, parallel-jobs,
      file-groups) and path-charset inputs (test-path, dockerfile-dir,
      project-name) validated in a setup-job gate and consumed via env: rather
      than direct ${{ }} interpolation, per GitHub script-injection guidance.
      Numeric inputs also bounded above (parallel-jobs/file-groups <= 64,
      timeout <= 360 GHA cap) to prevent catastrophic misconfiguration.
      Free-form inputs (docker-run-flags, runs-on, concurrency-group) remain
      caller-trusted and are documented as such.

-- Changes --
[Change] file-groups.sh always emits the `include` matrix shape (drops the
         legacy file-groups<=1 simple-form). num-groups<=1 omits group/files
         keys to keep matrix.group falsy in concurrency/artifact-name
         expressions — preserves v1.4.2 behavior for default consumers.
[Change] BATSMAN_CONTAINER_TEST_PATH header documents the no-space and
         filename-charset constraints that callers must honor.

- 1.4.2 | Apr 2026:

-- New Features --
[New] CI workflow: runs-on input for test jobs. Consumers can pass
      runs-on: 'self-hosted' to run tests on self-hosted runners.
      Default: 'ubuntu-latest' (no change required for existing consumers).

- 1.4.1 | Apr 2026:

-- Bug Fixes --
[Fix] CI workflow: BATS --jobs smoke test on deep-legacy targets. Bash 4.1/4.2
      silently fails parallel mode; smoke test verifies execution before enabling
      --jobs, falls back to serial with ::warning annotation on failure.

- 1.4.0 | Mar 2026:

-- New Features --
[New] CI workflow: file-groups input (default 1) — splits test files into N groups,
      each running in a separate GHA matrix job with isolated container state.
      Round-robin distribution by file, sorted by name (numbered convention).
      Consumers opt in: file-groups: 4 produces 8 OS × 4 groups = 32 parallel jobs.
[New] scripts/file-groups.sh — standalone round-robin file distributor, outputs
      GitHub Actions strategy.matrix JSON (os × group cross-product)
[New] scripts/install-parallel.sh — GNU parallel installer with TLS fallback
      (wget/curl) and SHA256 checksum verification for deep legacy OS
[New] GNU parallel in all 9 base Docker images — centos6 and ubuntu1204 gain
      parallel via standalone Perl script install
[New] 13 self-tests for file-group distribution logic

-- Bug Fixes --
[Fix] batsman_clean(): grep -E → grep -F for BATSMAN_PROJECT — eliminates regex
      metacharacter injection risk from project names
[Fix] batsman_run_parallel(): local declaration moved before for-loop — local
      inside loop body is misleading (bash scopes to function, not block)
